{"type":"message","id":"e7880dc0","parentId":"4090ef1a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:18:41.034Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d273x2co7dtt_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 161707\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE, Phase 1 IN PROGRESS\r\n2. CFI analysis complete, next is \"conditional content analysis\"\r\n3. The next experiment is clearly defined: test whether moderate-frequency tokens with high CFI are genuinely causal by comparing research content when token is present vs absent\r\n\r\nThis is the highest priority pending task according to the goals. I should implement this experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending experiment:\r\n- For tokens like \"compression\" (freq=199, CFI=0.995), \"causal\" (freq=162, CFI=0.981), \"phase\" (freq=187, CFI=0.946)\r\n- Split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups\r\n- Compare research content between groups\r\n- If no difference: CFI measures scaffolding. If yes: tokens are genuinely causal.\r\n\r\nI need to create a script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse history\r\n2. For each candidate token, finds pulse pairs where token appears in pulse N\r\n3. Compares the content of pulse N+1 between groups\r\n4. Quantifies whether there's a meaningful difference\r\n\r\nLet me write this analysis script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe conditional content analysis is the critical next experiment to distinguish CFI (pattern information) from true causal influence. I need to implement this empirically to resolve whether high-CFI tokens like \"compression\" and \"causal\" are genuine causal drivers or just scaffolding.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md` with a Python analysis script to test whether pulses containing high-CFI tokens show different next-pulse content than those without. This tests the core hypothesis: if content differs, tokens are causal; if identical, CFI measures scaffolding only.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Conditional Content Analysis\r\n\r\n**Purpose:** Distinguish Causal Information from Pattern Information\r\n\r\n**Hypothesis:**\r\n- If pulses with token T show systematically different next-pulse content than those without T → T is genuinely causal\r\n- If next-pulse content is identical regardless of T → CFI measures scaffolding only (constant-format artifact)\r\n\r\n**Methodology:**\r\n1. For each candidate token T, split pulse pairs into T-present and T-absent groups\r\n2. Extract key research terms from next-pulse for each group\r\n3. Compute Jaccard similarity between group vocabularies\r\n4. If Jaccard < 0.7: token is causal. If Jaccard ≥ 0.9: token is scaffolding.\r\n\r\n**Candidate Tokens (moderate frequency, high CFI):**\r\n- \"compression\" (freq=199, CFI=0.995)\r\n- \"causal\" (freq=162, CFI=0.981)\r\n- \"phase\" (freq=187, CFI=0.946)\r\n- \"token\" (freq=198, CFI=0.990)\r\n\r\n**Expected Results:**\r\n- \"Phase 1\" vs \"Phase 2\" likely causal (trajectory changes)\r\n- \"compression\" likely scaffolding (explains same concepts regardless)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nConditional Content Analysis for Causal vs Pattern Information\r\n\r\nFor each high-CFI token, compare next-pulse content when token is present vs absent.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nimport math\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"pulse_history\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in sorted(PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        content = f.read_text()\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            'file': f.name,\r\n            'content': content,\r\n            'lines': content.split('\\n')\r\n        })\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\ndef extract_research_terms(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful research terms (not formatting scaffolding).\"\"\"\r\n    # Filter out common scaffolding\r\n    stop_words = {'the', 'a', 'an', 'is', 'are', 'was', 'were', 'be', 'been',\r\n                  'and', 'or', 'but', 'in', 'on', 'at', 'to', 'for', 'of', 'with',\r\n                  'by', 'from', 'as', 'that', 'this', 'it', 'its', '##', '###'}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract words\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z]{4,}\\b', text.lower())\r\n    terms = [w for w in words if w not in stop_words and not w.isdigit()]\r\n    \r\n    # Count frequencies\r\n    freq = defaultdict(int)\r\n    for t in terms:\r\n        freq[t] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Return top 20 terms\r\n    return set(sorted(freq.keys(), key=lambda x: freq[x], reverse=True)[:20])\r\n\r\ndef jaccard_similarity(set1, set2):\r\n    \"\"\"Jaccard similarity between two sets.\"\"\"\r\n    if not set1 and not set2:\r\n        return 1.0\r\n    intersection = len(set1 & set2)\r\n    union = len(set1 | set2)\r\n    return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\r\n\r\ndef analyze_token(pulses, token):\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze conditional content for a specific token.\"\"\"\r\n    present_next = []\r\n    absent_next = []\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(pulses) - 1):\r\n        current_content = pulses[i]['content'].lower()\r\n        next_content = pulses[i + 1]['content']\r\n        next_terms = extract_research_terms(next_content)\r\n        \r\n        if token.lower() in current_content:\r\n            present_next.append(next_terms)\r\n        else:\r\n            absent_next.append(next_terms)\r\n    \r\n    if not present_next or\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 16:17:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383521031}}
